{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/applicationprotocol\/addmainoption(entries:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationProtocol"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Adds main option entries to be handled by "},{"code":"application","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"addMainOption","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"entries","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"GOptionEntry","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":">!)"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function is comparable to "},{"code":"g_option_context_add_main_entries()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"After the commandline arguments are parsed, the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[Application](\/\/documentation\/gio\/application\/onhandlelocaloptions(flags:handler:) signal will be emitted.  At this","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"point, the application can inspect the values pointed to by ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"arg_data"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in the given ","type":"text"},{"code":"GOptionEntrys","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Unlike [OptionContext](\/\/documentation\/glib\/optioncontext, ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Application","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" supports giving a "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"arg_data"},{"type":"text","text":" for a non-callback [OptionEntry](\/\/documentation\/glib\/optionentry.  This results in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"argument in question being packed into a [VariantDict](\/\/documentation\/glib\/variantdict which is also"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"passed to [Application](\/\/documentation\/gio\/application\/onhandlelocaloptions(flags:handler:), where it can be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"inspected and modified.  If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"handlesCommandLine"},{"text":" is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"set, then the resulting dictionary is sent to the primary instance,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"where ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_application_command_line_get_options_dict()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will return it.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"As it has been passed outside the process at this point, the types of all","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"values in the options dict must be checked before being used."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This “packing” is done according to the type of the argument –"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"booleans for normal flags, strings for strings, bytestrings for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"filenames, etc.  The packing only occurs if the flag is given (ie: we","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"do not pack a “false” [Variant](\/\/documentation\/glib\/variant in the case that a flag is missing).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In general, it is recommended that all commandline arguments are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parsed locally.  The options dictionary should then be used to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"transmit the result of the parsing to the primary instance, where","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_dict_lookup()"},{"text":" can be used.  For local options, it is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"possible to either use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"arg_data"},{"text":" in the usual way, or to consult (and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"potentially remove) the option from the options dictionary.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This function is new in GLib 2.40.  Before then, the only real choice","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"was to send all of the commandline arguments (options and all) to the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"primary instance for handling.  "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Application","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" ignored them completely"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on the local side.  Calling this function “opts in” to the new","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"behaviour, and in particular, means that unrecognized options will be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"treated as errors.  Unrecognized options have never been ignored when"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"handlesCommandLine","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is unset.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If [Application](\/\/documentation\/gio\/application\/onhandlelocaloptions(flags:handler:) needs to see the list of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"filenames, then the use of [OPTION_REMAINING](\/\/documentation\/glib\/option_remaining is recommended.  If","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"arg_data"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" then [OPTION_REMAINING](\/\/documentation\/glib\/option_remaining can be used as a key into","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the options dictionary.  If you do use [OPTION_REMAINING](\/\/documentation\/glib\/option_remaining then you","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"need to handle these arguments for yourself because once they are","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"consumed, they will no longer be visible to the default handling","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(which treats them as filenames to be opened)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is important to use the proper GVariant format when retrieving"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the options with "},{"code":"g_variant_dict_lookup()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"for ","type":"text"},{"code":"none","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"b"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"for [string](\/\/documentation\/glib\/string, use "},{"code":"&s","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"for [CInt](\/\/documentation\/glib\/cint, use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"i"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"for [int64](\/\/documentation\/glib\/int64, use "},{"code":"x","type":"codeVoice"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"for [CDouble](\/\/documentation\/glib\/cdouble, use ","type":"text"},{"code":"d","type":"codeVoice"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"for [String](\/\/documentation\/glib\/string, use "},{"code":"^&ay","type":"codeVoice"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"for [string_array](\/\/documentation\/glib\/string_array, use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"^a&s"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"for [filename_array](\/\/documentation\/glib\/filename_array, use ","type":"text"},{"code":"^a&ay","type":"codeVoice"}]}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationProtocol\/addMainOption(entries:)"},"metadata":{"extendedModule":"GIO","symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:3GIO19ApplicationProtocolPAAE13addMainOption7entriesySPySo13_GOptionEntryVGSg_tF","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"addMainOption","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"entries"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"GOptionEntry","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">!)","kind":"text"}],"title":"addMainOption(entries:)","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Method"},"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Application":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Application"}],"title":"Application","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GApplication"},{"type":"text","text":" is the core class for application support."}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Application","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Application","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/application"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/ApplicationProtocol":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ApplicationProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/applicationprotocol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"code":"GApplication","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is the core class for application support."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationProtocol","title":"ApplicationProtocol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ApplicationProtocol","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/ApplicationProtocol/addMainOption(entries:)":{"abstract":[{"text":"Adds main option entries to be handled by ","type":"text"},{"code":"application","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"addMainOption"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"entries","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"GOptionEntry","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">!)","kind":"text"}],"type":"topic","title":"addMainOption(entries:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ApplicationProtocol\/addMainOption(entries:)","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/applicationprotocol\/addmainoption(entries:)","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol"}}}